Today's Topic 1 — High-Level Design (HLD) Basics

      This is probably the most important interview round at Google for L5.      
      Many engineers fail because they jump directly into technologies.      
      Google wants to evaluate how you think, not how many AWS services you know.
      
      What is High-Level Design?
                      High-Level Design describes the entire architecture of a system.

Instead of talking about code...

You talk about

                components
                services
                databases
                communication
                scaling
                reliability

Think of it as designing an entire city instead of designing one house.

Imagine Google asks

Design YouTube.                  
                  They don't expect code.                  
                    They expect architecture.

For example:

                                      Users
                                      
                                           │
                                           ▼
                                      
                                      Load Balancer
                                      
                                           │
                                           ▼
                                      
                                      API Gateway
                                      
                                           │
                                           ▼
                                      
                                      Video Service
                                      User Service
                                      Recommendation Service
                                      Comment Service
                                      
                                           │
                                           ▼
                                      
                                      Databases
                                      Cache
                                      CDN
                                      Object Storage

    Notice:    
            No Java.            
            No Spring Boot.            
            No SQL queries.            
            Only architecture.

What Google evaluates

          During HLD they observe whether you think like a distributed systems engineer.

They score:

1. Requirement Gathering ⭐
              Many candidates immediately start drawing diagrams.
              
              Google expects you to ask questions first.              
              Example:
              
              Design Instagram.              
              Before drawing anything...

    Ask:              
              How many users?              
              Daily Active Users?              
              Photos only?              
              Videos?              
              Stories?              
              Search?              
              Messaging?              
              Expected QPS?              
              Latency requirements?              
              Availability?              
              Consistency?              
              Storage size?
              
              This is the biggest difference between average and strong candidates.

2. APIs
        Example:                  
                  POST /upload                  
                  GET /feed                  
                  GET /video/{id}                  
                  POST /comment
        
        Interviewers want to know        
        How clients communicate with your system.

3. Components
              Break the system into services.              
              Example:
              
                      Authentication Service                      
                      Video Service                      
                      Notification Service                      
                      Search Service                      
                      Recommendation Service
4. Database
              Choose wisely.              
              SQL?              
              NoSQL?              
              Object Storage?              
              Graph DB?              
              Cache?

5. Scalability                
                Can your system handle                
                100 users?                
                1000?                
                1 million?                
                100 million?                
                1 billion?

6. Reliability
            What happens if a server dies?            
            Does everything stop?            
            Or continue working?

7. Bottlenecks
        
        Every design has bottlenecks.
        
        Google wants you to identify them before they ask.





